SIMPLE: frenzy
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frenzy
<hw>Fren"zy</hw> <pr>(fr⟦ecr⟧n"z⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Frenzies</plw> <pr>(fr⟦ecr⟧n"z⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[OE. <ets>frenesie</ets>, <ets>fransey</ets>, F.
<ets>fr⟦eacute⟧n⟦eacute⟧sie</ets>, L. <ets>phrenesis</ets>, fr. Gr.
<grk>fre`nhsis</grk> for <grk>freni^tis</grk> disease of the mind,
phrenitis, fr. <grk>frhn</grk> mind. Cf. <er>Frantic</er>,
<er>Phrenitis</er>.]</ety> <def>Any violent agitation of the mind
approaching to distraction; violent and temporary derangement of the
mental faculties; madness; rage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All else is towering <qex>frenzy</qex> and distraction.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The poet's eye in a fine <qex>frenzy</qex> rolling.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Insanity; lunacy; madness; derangement;
alienation; aberration; delirium. See <er>Insanity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frenzy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Frenzy
<hw>Fren"zy</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Mad; frantic.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They thought that some <qex>frenzy</qex> distemper had got into
his head.</q> <rj><qau>Bunyan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frenzy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Frenzy
<hw>Fren"zy</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To affect with frenzy; to drive
to madness</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Frenzying</xex>
anguish.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Southey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>frenzy-free</ent>⟦br⟧
